4.95/5  rDev +11.5%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5Orange highlights in hazy, deep rose-colored liquid. A soapy ring of pink embraces the wall of the glass. Sexy earth aromas, like honey-drenched slate launch disturbing arcs of cracked, toasted mustard seed. All of this leads to aromas of raspberries of course, but it is a pile of sticky, mashed, partially rotting fruit as much as it is fresh and clean. Plump, bulky texture, citric jelly flavor and outlying gas detail forms the shape and structure of this beer.
