Enjoyed as a 4oz sample at the Belgian Beer Fest 2004. They were out of Gueuze, so this was sampled instead. Man, I'm glad I did. My first TRUE fruit lambic! Pours a unique, glowing, deep, opaque red. Amazingly deep red! No head, very light carbonation, despite being on draft. Regardless, a beautiful beer. Smell is sweet and of raspberries. Taste is remarkably sour, bold, tangy, and almost uniformly raspberry flavored.Though I lack a deep base knowledge for comparison, I was told this is one of the best fruit lambics, and I believe it. Truly excellent. 582 charactersRocketWidget, Mar 26, 2005
